comment: Iguodala (GSW) cleanly knocks the ball away from Warren (PHO).
Tucker (PHO) makes incidental contact with Thompson's (GSW) leg while diving for the loose ball.
Morris (PHO) does not establish legal guarding position and is still sliding to his left prior to the start of Thompson's (GSW) upward shooting motion.
Bogut (GSW) sets the screen on Goodwin (PHO) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Bogut (GSW) sets the screen on Goodwin (PHO) and continues backing into him, not giving him the opportunity to change direction.
Iguodala (GSW) and Morris (PHO) briefly engage away from the ball.
Bogut (GSW) does not affect Tucker's (PHO) RSBQ on his baseline drive.
Morris (PHO) jumps vertically and maintains legal guarding position as he defends Barnes' (GSW) shot attempt.
Bogut (GSW) dislodges Tucker (PHO) by pushing him with two hands to the back and the push affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Thompson (GSW) avoids contact with Morris (PHO) who stick his hip out in an attempt to set a screen.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Curry's (GSW) field goal was a 3 pointer was upheld.
LHH shows Thompson (GSW) makes incidental contact with Bledsoe's (PHO) shoulder during his layup attempt.
Speights (GSW) sets the screen on Goodwin (PHO) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
RATR and RHH show Bledsoe (PHO) cleanly knocks the ball away from Barnes (GSW) twice prior to Barnes regaining control and making the shot.
